Challenge 32: Minimum Meeting Rooms
What to do:
Given an array of meeting intervals, find the minimum number of conference rooms required.
Example Input:
intervals = [[0,30],[5,10],[15,20]]
Example Output:
2
Explanation:
Two rooms are needed:
•	Room 1: [0,30] 
•	Room 2: [5,10] and [15,20] (non-overlapping in the same room) 
